<hr>
<div class="container" style="font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif;">
<p>
    BEST is a non- profitable organisation. <strong>BEST</strong> indicates <b>B</b>asic education, <b>E</b>nergy savings,
<b>S</b>afety and <b>T</b>o give.
</p>
<p>
    It was established in the year 2016 to promote healthy lifestyle among all through different
ways. It's main center is at Barrackpore, West Bengal, India.
</p>
<div class="card border-info">
    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ">
      <li class="list-group-item border-info">It conducts one day workshop and activity oriented classes on basic education, proper
        utilization of energy, safety about food, health, household and others in different formal
        educational institutions like schools, colleges etc.</li>
      <li class="list-group-item border-info">BEST publishes a yearly magazine named 'ARJAMA' during the festive month of
        Autumn. This magazine spreads the fragrance of proper life style through various
        positive messages of the valuable articles silently.</li>
      <li class="list-group-item border-info">Besides this, BEST provides Food Bank & Cloth Bank also. In every month the members
        go to take classes in different slum areas, rural areas and interior regions to nurture their
        healthy habitsfor a overall developed lifestyle. After the class dry food or new/ old clothes
        (donated) are distributed among the pupils. The students are divided into two groups
        according to their age groups- 5 to 12 years are considered as junior section and 12 to
        18 years are classified as senior section. Classes are taken separately according to the
        above- mentioned section. After the class there is a time slotting for guardians to discuss
        the class topic and the members interact with the guardians so as they can follow the
        guidelines given in the class.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item border-info">BEST has inaugurated a library for spreading the aroma of knowledge among all.</li>
    </ul>
</div>
